Graphics

   Great graphics placeholders and tools to turn that squared game into a
   picasso painting

Assets/Placeholders

     * [http://graphicburger.com/mobile-game-gui/]2D Cartoon Mobile Game
       UI Pack - cartoon user interface asset pack. It comes as a layered
       psd file.
     * [http://7soul1.deviantart.com/art/420-Pixel-Art-Icons-for-RPG-12989
       2453]420 Pixel Art Icons for RPGs - Set of 420 RPG icons, free for
       commercial use.
     * [https://www.blender-models.com/]Blender 3D models - 3D models,
       particle systems/effects
     * ¸ [http://www.textures.com/]CGTextures - A large collection of
       textures.
     * ¸ [https://www.gamedevmarket.net/]GameDev Market - a
       community-driven marketplace that connects indie game developers
       with talented asset creators.
     * [http://game-icons.net/]Games-Icons Set - free icons for your
       games.
     * [https://poly.google.com/]Google Poly - Searchable database of 3D
       models with rotatable previews. (Only remixable models are
       downloadable.)
     * [http://iconmonstr.com/]Iconmonstr - Another free icons resource
       for your games.
     * ¸ [http://kenney.nl/assets]Kenney Assets - Royalty free assets
     * [http://lpc.opengameart.org/]Liberated Pixel Cup assets - Free
       graphic assets of the Liberated Pixel Cup (LPC) held by the
       OpenGameArt forums
     * [https://openclipart.org/]OpenClipart - Collection of free
       cliparts.
     * [http://opengameart.org/]OpenGameArt - a media repository intended
       for use with free software game projects.
     * ° [http://oryxdesignlab.com/]Oryx Design Lab - Cheap high quality
       royalty free sprites
     * ¸ [http://www.plaintextures.com/]PlainTextures - Free high
       resolution textures, brushes and photos
     * [http://www.reinerstilesets.de/]Reiner's Tilesets - A blog with
       free 2D and 3D graphics.
     * [https://sketchfab.com/]Sketchfab - Publish & embed interactive 3D
       models.
     * [http://www.widgetworx.com/spritelib/]SpriteLib - a collection of
       static and animated graphic objects (also commonly known as
       sprites).
     * [http://www.stickpng.com/]StickyPNG - Free transparent PNG images.
     * [http://www.textureking.com/]TextureKing - Free material stock
       textures
     * [http://arnaud.ile.nc/cantree/generator.php]Tree Generator - An
       Online tree generator.
     * ¸ [http://www.vecteezy.com/]Vecteezy - Free Vector Art.
     * [https://www.yobi3d.com/]Yobi3D - Free 3D model search engine.

Spritesheet Tools

     * [https://github.com/scriptum/Cheetah-Texture-Packer]Cheetah-Texture
       -Packer - High efficient and fast 2D bin packing tool
     * [http://www.humanbalance.net/gale/us/]GraphicsGale - Animation
       graphic editor easy to use.
     * [https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/wiki/Texture-packer]Libgdx
       Texture Packer - Texture Packer built into Libgdx
     * [http://kvazars.com/littera]Littera - Bitmap font generator
     * [http://renderhjs.net/shoebox/]ShoeBox - Adobe Air based app with
       game and ui related tools.
     * [https://github.com/nickgravelyn/SpriteSheetPacker/]Sprite Sheet
       Packer - Combine multiple images into a single sprite sheet and
       generate a txt map of it.
     * ¸ [https://www.codeandweb.com/texturepacker]TexturePacker - Great
       spritesheet creation editor.

Bitmap Compression

     * [http://pngmini.com/]ImageAlpha -- Mac OS X GUI for pngquant and
       other tools
     * ¸ [https://kraken.io/]Kraken.io - robust, ultra-fast image
       optimizer and compressor with best-in-class algorithms.
     * [http://pnggauntlet.com/]PNGGauntlet - Smash PNGs for faster sites
     * [https://pngquant.org/PNGoo.0.1.1.zip]PNGoo - Windows GUI for batch
       conversion.
     * [http://nukesaq88.github.io/Pngyu/]Pngyu - simple PNG image file
       compression tool.
     * [http://www.fnordware.com/superpng/]SuperPNG Photoshop plug-in --
       Mac and Windows. Comparison with "Save for Web"
     * ¸ [https://tinypng.com/]TinyPNG - Advanced lossy compression for
       PNG images that preserves full alpha transparency.

Texture Tools

     * ° [https://www.filterforge.com/]FilterForge - A plugin for Adobe
       Photoshop that allows you to build your own filters.
     * ° [http://www.pixplant.com/]PixPlant - PixPlant is a smart 3D
       texturing tool that creates high quality normal, displacement,
       specular maps and seamless textures from photos.
     * ° [http://www.seamlesstexturegenerator.com/]STG - a tool for
       creating professional seamlessly-tileable textures from photographs
       quickly and easily.

Character Generators

     * [http://charas-project.net/index.php]Charas - Charas is a charset
       generator for RPG Maker.
     * [http://www.geocities.jp/kurororo4/looseleaf/]Loose Leaf - Sprite
       character generator
     * [http://gaurav.munjal.us/Universal-LPC-Spritesheet-Character-Genera
       tor]Universal LPC Sprite Sheet Character Generator - Sprite
       character generator based on the LPC (Liberated Pixel Cup) graphics

Tile/Level Editors

     * [http://arraypainter.com/]ArrayPainter - Array Painter is the
       easiest and fastest way to make 2D arrays ready for copy pasting
       into your own program.
     * ° [http://pixelatto.com/]AutoTileGen - AutoTileGen is an automatic
       tileset generator for 2D game terrains.
     * [http://www.ogmoeditor.com/]OGMO Editor - generic level editor.
     * [https://github.com/UnderwaterApps/overlap2d/]Overlap2D - a 2D
       level and UI editor with an engine agnostic philosophy.
     * [http://www.mapeditor.org/]Tiled - free, easy to use and flexible
       tile map editor.

Animation

     * ° [http://loopengo.free.fr/]Fusion Character Animator - small tool
       for Clickteam Fusion 2.5 to facilitate the animation of 2D
       character sprites for developers.
     * ° [http://esotericsoftware.com/]Spine - Spine is dedicated to 2D
       animation, providing an efficient workflow both for creating
       amazing animation and for integrating it into your games.
     * ° [http://www.brashmonkey.com/spriter.htm]Spriter - Modern tool for
       sprite animation.
     * [http://dragonbones.effecthub.com/]DragonBones - The Open Source 2D
       skeleton animation solution for Flash
     * [http://gree.github.io/lwf/]LWF - Lightweight SWF. LWF is an
       animation engine which can play animation data converted from FLASH
       contents in HTML5, Unity, Cocos2d-x, iOS UIKit, and more.

Vector/Image Editor

     * ° [https://affinity.serif.com/de/designer]Affinity Designer -
       Vector graphics editor with a bunch of features which also supports
       Adobe file formats
     * ° [https://affinity.serif.com/de/photo]Affinity Photo - Photo and
       raster graphics editor which works together with Adobe file formats
       and Affinity Designer
     * ¸ [http://www.aseprite.org/]Aseprite - animated sprite editor &
       pixel art tool.
     * [http://www.gimp.org/]Gimp - GNU Image Manipulation Program. It is
       a freely distributed piece of software for such tasks as photo
       retouching, image composition and image authoring.
     * [https://inkscape.org/en/]Inkscape - An open-source vector graphics
       editor similar to Adobe Illustrator, Corel Draw, Freehand, or Xara
       X.
     * [https://krita.org/]Krita - Krita is a professional FREE and open
       source painting program. It is made by artists that want to see
       affordable art tools for everyone.
     * [http://multipaint.kameli.net/]Multipaint - A cross-platform (Win,
       Linux, Mac) image editor/painter which covers the color limitations
       of 8-bit machines (like C64, ZX Spectrum etc.)
     * ° [http://thebloomapp.com/]Ormr - Ormr is a fast, light-weight,
       cross-platform procedural graphics editor.
     * ¸ [http://www.getpaint.net/]Paint.NET - Paint.NET is free image and
       photo editing software for PCs that run Windows.
     * ° [http://www.pickleeditor.com/]Pickle - Another Pixel art Editor.
     * [http://www.piskelapp.com/]PiskelApp - Free Online Pixel Art and
       Animated Sprite Tool.
     * [http://www.pixelmator.com/]Pixelmator - Full-featured image
       editing app for the Mac
     * ° [https://github.com/Pixen/Pixen]Pixen - Pixel Art Editor for OSX
     * [http://p1.untergrund.net/]project one - A picture converter and
       editor for the Commodore 64 covering different graphics mode of
       this computer. Windows only
     * ° [http://www.pxl8.it/]PXL8 - A cross platform (Windows, Mac,
       Linux) pixel art editor in development which aims to be distraction
       free
     * ° [http://pyxeledit.com/]PyxelEdit - Pixel art editor designed to
       make it fun and easy to make tilesets, levels and animations.
     * [http://csdb.dk/release/?id=75871]Timanthes - A pixel art editor
       for the Commodore 64 computer running on Windows
     * [http://charas-project.net/index.php]Charas - Charas is a charset
       generator for RPG Maker.
     * [http://www.geocities.jp/kurororo4/looseleaf/]Loose Leaf - Sprite
       character generator
     * [http://gaurav.munjal.us/Universal-LPC-Spritesheet-Character-Genera
       tor]Universal LPC Sprite Sheet Character Generator - Sprite
       character generator based on the LPC (Liberated Pixel Cup) graphics
     * [http://www.spritemate.com/]Spritemate - Online Editor for
       Commodore 64 Sprites
     * ° [http://pixelatorapp.com/]Pixelator - Turn any image into fancy
       pixel-art

Modeling

     * [http://www.blender.org/]Blender
     * [http://www.makehuman.org/]MakeHuman
     * [http://pixologic.com/sculptris/]sculptris
     * ° [http://www.autodesk.com/products/maya/overview]Maya
     * ° [http://www.autodesk.com/products/3ds-max/overview]3ds Max
     * ° [https://www.foundry.com/products/modo]modo
     * [https://clara.io/]Clara.io

Terrain Generators

     * [http://www.artifexterra.com/]Artifex Terra - Terrain editor for
       easy and sophisticated landscape painting and editing
     * [https://entardev.wordpress.com/other-projects/canyon-terrain-edito
       r/]Canyon Terrain Editor - Create quality, realistic terrain
       quickly and intuitively
     * [https://sourceforge.net/projects/fracplanet/]Fracplanet - Fractal
       planet and terrain generator
     * [http://nemesis.thewavelength.net/index.php?p=8]Nem TG - 3D terrain
       generator
     * ° [http://www.world-machine.com/]World Machine - Procedural terrain
       creation, simulations of nature, and interactive editing

Voxel Editors

     * [https://github.com/guillaumechereau/goxel]goxel
     * [https://ephtracy.github.io/]MagicaVoxel
     * [http://kyucon.com/qblock/]Q-Block
     * [http://sproxel.blogspot.com.br/]Sproxel
     * [https://blackflux.com/index.php]VoxelShop

Code

   Set of game frameworks, engines and platforms

Engines and Frameworks

     * [http://2dengine.com/]Agen - Cross-Platform framework for making 2D
       games with Lua, compatible iOS, Mac and Windows devices.
     * [http://liballeg.org/]Allegro - Allegro 4 & 5 are cross-platform,
       open source, game programming libraries, primarily for C and C++
       developers.
     * [http://www.andengine.org/]AndEngine - 2D Android Game Engine
     * [http://azul3d.org/]Azul3D - A 3D engine written in Go.
     * [http://bacon2d.com/]Bacon2D - A framework to ease 2D game
       development, providing ready-to-use QML elements representing basic
       game entities needed by most of games.
     * [https://github.com/bladecoder/bladecoder-adventure-engine]Bladecod
       er - Classic point and click adventure game engine and editor.
     * ¸ [http://www.blend4web.com/]Blend4Web - A Javascript framework for
       creating and displaying interactive 3D computer graphics in web
       browsers.
     * [http://www.blitzbasic.com/Products/blitz3d.php]Blitz3D 3D
       basic-like programming language for fast 3D desktop games.
     * [http://box2d.org/]Box2D - A 2D Physics Engine for Games.
     * [http://bulletphysics.org/wordpress/]Bullet - Real-time physics
       simulation.
     * [https://github.com/CRYTEK-CRYENGINE/CRYENGINE]CRYENGINE - A pay
       what you want next gen 3D game engine written in C++.
     * [https://github.com/netonjm/ChipmunkSharp]Chipmunk C# - C#
       implementation of the Chipmunk2D lib.
     * [https://chipmunk-physics.net/]Chipmunk2D - A fast and lightweight
       2D game physics library.
     * [https://libcinder.org/]Cinder - Cinder is a community-developed,
       free and open source library for professional-quality creative
       coding in C++.
     * [http://cocos2d-x.org/docs/editors_and_tools/creator/index.html]Coc
       os Creator - Cocos Creator, a free cross-platform game development
       editor supporting Cocos2d-js, helps developers build 2D and 3D game
       scenes, edit game UI and other game resources quickly and
       efficiency.
     * [https://github.com/los-cocos/cocos]Cocos2D - graphic library for
       games and multimedia, for python language
     * [http://cocos2d-x.org/]Cocos2d-x - a C++ OpenGL 2D and 3D game
       engine. Uses C++ but has JS and Lua bindings. Target all the major
       mobile platforms and operating systems. Additional tools CocoStudio
       and Cocos Code IDE.
     * ¸ [https://www.scirra.com/]Construct 2 - an HTML5 game maker,
       meaning you are not actually writing JavaScript. Instead, you use
       actions, events and conditions to do the heavy lifting.
     * ° [http://www.ambiera.com/coppercube/]CopperCube3D - CopperCube is
       an all-in-one 3D game engine.Very easy to use.
     * [http://coquette.maryrosecook.com/]Coquette - A micro framework for
       JavaScript games. Handles collision detection, the game update
       loop, canvas rendering, and keyboard and mouse input.
     * [https://coronalabs.com/]Corona SDK - A Cross-Platform Mobile App
       Development for iOS and Android.
     * [https://github.com/Circular-Studios/Dash]Dash - A free and open 3D
       game engine written in D.
     * [http://www.defold.com/]Defold - Free 2D Game Engine for
       Cross-Platform Publishing
     * [http://duality.adamslair.net/]Duality - C# / OpenGL 2D Game Engine
       that comes with visual editor.
     * [https://github.com/ajhager/engi]ENGi - A multi-platform 2D game
       library for Go.
     * [https://hajimehoshi.github.io/ebiten/]Ebiten - A dead simple 2D
       game library in Go.
     * [http://impactjs.com/ejecta]Ejecta - A Fast, Open Source
       JavaScript, Canvas & Audio Implementation for iOS.
     * [http://enchantjs.com/]EnchantJS - A simple JavaScript framework
       for creating games and apps.
     * [https://github.com/AlmasB/FXGL]FXGL - A JavaFX/Kotlin game engine
       for Win/Mac/Linux.
     * [https://github.com/VelcroPhysics/VelcroPhysics]Farseer - a
       collision detection system with realistic physics responses.
     * [http://useflashpunk.net/]FlashPunk - free ActionScript 3 library
       designed for developing 2D Flash games.
     * [http://flixel.org/index.html]Flixel - an open source game-making
       written in ActionScript3.
     * ° [http://www.yoyogames.com/studio]GameMaker - GameMaker
       accommodates the creation of cross-platform video games using drag
       and drop or a scripting language known as Game Maker Language,
       which can be used to develop more advanced games that could not be
       created just by using the drag and drop features.
     * ¸ [https://gamesalad.com/]GameSalad - Game Creation Engine for Mac
       and Windows.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/]Gideros - A Cross-Platform framework to
       create Mobile Apps and games for iOS, Android using Lua programming
       language.
     * [http://www.godotengine.org/]Godot - An advanced, feature-packed,
       multi-platform 2D and 3D open-source game engine.
     * [http://www.planimeter.org/grid-sdk/]Grid - Lua Game Engine.
     * [http://www.havok.com/vision-engine/]Havok Vision - a
       cross-platform game engine that provides a powerful and versatile
       multi-platform runtime technology.
     * [http://haxeflixel.com/]HaxeFlixel - Create cross-platform games
       easier and free.
     * [http://www.haxor.xyz/]Haxor - Combine the power of HaXe language
       and HTML5+WebGL to easily develop powerful applications that can
       run in any modern browser.
     * [http://www.eyelead.com/hive/]Hive3D - Real Time Collaboration 3D
       engine.
     * [http://www.horde3d.org/]Horde3D - small open source 3D rendering
       engine.
     * ° [http://impactjs.com/]ImpactJS - Impact is a JavaScript Game
       Engine that allows you to develop stunning HTML5 Games for desktop
       and mobile browsers.
     * [http://inform7.com/]Inform7 - A design system for interactive
       fiction based on natural language.
     * [http://www.inklestudios.com/ink/]Ink - Scripting language for
       writing interactive narrative.
     * [http://irrlicht.sourceforge.net/]Irrlicht - open source high
       performance realtime 3D engine written in C++.
     * [http://www.jpct.net/]JPCT - jPCT is a 3D engine for desktop Java
       and Google's Android.
     * [https://code.google.com/p/jitterphysics/]Jitter - a fast and
       lightweight physics engine written in C#.
     * [https://github.com/rxi/juno]Juno - Framework for making 2D games
       with chunky pixels in Lua
     * [http://kivent.org/]Kivent - A 2D game framework for Kivy.
     * [http://kivy.org/]Kivy - Cross platform Python framework for
       creating apps and games for Linux, Windows, OS X, Android and iOS
     * [http://www.kiwijs.org/]KiwiJS - a fun and friendly Open Source
       HTML5 Game Engine. Some people call it the WordPress of HTML5 game
       engines
     * [https://libgdx.badlogicgames.com/]LibGDX - Powerful (totally free)
       library for Java, code once and run the game on desktop, Android,
       Web, and iOS.
     * [http://www.limejs.com/]LimeJS - HTML5 game framework for building
       fast, native-experience games for all modern touchscreens and
     * [http://loomsdk.com/]Loom SDK - 2D mobile app and game framework
       with live reload of code and assets, AS3/JS/C#-like scripting
       language, and powerful 2D rendering and UI framework. Open source
       with paid "Turbo" service.
     * [https://aws.amazon.com/pt/lumberyard/]Lumberyard - Amazon
       Lumberyard is a free AAA game engine deeply integrated
     * [https://github.com/nem0/LumixEngine]LumixEngine - 3D Game engine
       built on C++.
     * [https://github.com/lums-proj/Lums]Lums - A 2D / 3D framework
       written in C++11. Very efficient and modern. Still under heavy
       development.
     * [http://love2d.org/]LÖVE - Lua 2D Game Engine.
     * [https://github.com/GearChicken/MINX]MINX - Open Source 2D game
       framework written in C++ (to the style of XNA)
     * [http://getmoai.com/]MOAI - Cross-Platform framework designed for
       pro game developers to create iOS, Android, Windows, Linux, Chrome
       and OSX games using C++, OpenGL and Lua scripting.
     * [http://brm.io/matter-js/]Matter.js - a 2D physics engine for the
       web.
     * [http://melonjs.org/]MelonJS - open source light-weight HTML5 game
       engine.
     * [http://www.monkey-x.com/]Monkey X - Multi-platform programming
       language and cross-compiler, aimed at fast game programming.
     * [http://www.monogame.net/]Monogame - Open Source implementation of
       the Microsoft XNA 4 Framework.
     * [https://www.nodebox.net/]NodeBox - a family of Python tools to
       create generative design.
     * [http://www.ode.org/]ODE - ODE is an open source, high performance
       library for simulating rigid body dynamics.
     * [http://www.ogre3d.org/]Ogre3D - is a scene-oriented, real-time,
       flexible 3D rendering engine (as opposed to a game engine) written
       in C++.
     * [http://www.openfl.org/]OpenFL - Open Source Haxe Engine for making
       multi-platform games.
     * [http://www.openra.net/]OpenRA - OpenRA is a Libre/Free Real Time
       Strategy Game Engine.
     * [http://origamijs.com/docs]Origamijs - Lightweight Library to
       create using HTML5 Canvas.
     * ° [http://www.lexaloffle.com/pico-8.php]PICO-8 - A fantasy console
       for making, sharing and playing tiny games and other computer
       programs.
     * [https://www.panda3d.org/]Panda3D - a framework for 3D rendering
       and game development for Python and C++ programs.
     * [http://www.pandajs.net/]PandaJS - Open Source HTML5 Engine.
     * [http://phaser.io/]Phaser - free and fast 2D game framework for
       making HTML5 games for desktop and mobile web browsers, supporting
       Canvas and WebGL rendering.
     * [http://www.piston.rs/]Piston - a modular open source game engine
       written in Rust.
     * ¸ [https://twitter.com/PixelVision8]Pixel Vision 8 - a framework
       designed to simulate your favorite 8-bit consoles.
     * [http://www.pixijs.com/]PixiJS - is a newcomer HTML5 game renderer
       - first released in early 2013. A main appeal of the engine is its
       use of WebGL for faster performance. If WebGL isn't supported, the
       engine falls back to standard canvas.
     * [http://piqnt.com/planck.js/]Planck.js - 2D JavaScript physics
       engine for cross-platform HTML5 game development.
     * ¸ [https://playcanvas.com/]PlayCanvas - A WebGL Game Engine.
     * [http://polycode.org/]Polycode - Open-Source Framework for creating
       games in C++ (with Lua bindings).
     * [https://www.processing.org/]Processing - Processing is a
       programming language, development environment for artists,
       designers, researchers.
     * [http://www.puzzlescript.net/]PuzzleScript - open-source HTML5
       puzzle game engine.
     * [http://pygame.org/hifi.html]PyGame - a 2D game engine in Python.
     * [http://www.qiciengine.com/]QICI - Efficient web-based tool for
       creating HTML5 games.
     * ° [http://www.rpgmakerweb.com/]RPGMaker - series of programs for
       the development of role-playing games.
     * [https://github.com/Rajawali/Rajawali]Rajawali - Android OpenGL ES
       2.0/3.0 Engine
     * [http://www.renpy.org/]Ren'Py - An open-source visual novel engine
       using the Python language in simplified form. It supports Windows,
       Mac OS X, Linux, Android and iOS.
     * [http://rpgboss.com/]Rpgboss - A 2d rpg game engine and editor
       based on scala and libgdx. Ease of use, with no programming
       knowledge.
     * [http://libsdl.org/]SDL - SDL is a cross-platform library designed
       to provide low level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, joystick,
       and graphics hardware via OpenGL and Direct3D.
     * [http://www.sfml-dev.org/]SFML - Simple and Fast Multimedia
       Library.
     * [http://springrts.com/]Spring - A powerful free cross-platform RTS
       engine.
     * [https://developer.apple.com/documentation/spritekit]SpriteKit -
       iOS/Mac 2D Game Engine.
     * [http://piqnt.com/stage.js/]Stage.js - Lightweight and fast 2D
       HTML5 rendering and layout engine for cross-platform game
       development.
     * [http://gamua.com/starling/]Starling - The GPU powered 2D Flash API
     * ¸ [http://www.stencyl.com/]Stencyl - a game creation platform that
       allows users to create 2D video games for computers, mobile
       devices, and the web.
     * [https://sparklinlabs.itch.io/superpowers]Superpowers - HTML5
       Collaborative 2D/3D Game Maker
     * [https://tic.computer/]TIC-80 - TIC-80 is a fantasy computer for
       making, playing and sharing tiny games.
     * [http://threejs.org/]Three.js - Javascript 3D Library.
     * [http://biz.turbulenz.com/developers]Turbulenz - Turbulenz offers
       the ability to build, publish, iterate and monetise high-quality
       games that react like no others, with immersive 3D effects and
       real-time physics that open up a whole new world of unprecedented
       and extraordinary web content.
     * [http://twinery.org/]Twine - Downloadable or browser-based game
       development platform that allows users to create linked story
       paths. Not just text-based, Twine supports music, images, and sound
       effects. Very little coding knowledge required for basic text
       adventure games.
     * ¸ [http://unity3d.com/]Unity 3D - A development engine for the
       creation of 2D and 3D games and interactive content.
     * [https://www.unrealengine.com/]Unreal Engine 4 - the new game
       engine technology developed by Epic Games.
     * [http://urho3d.github.io/]Urho3D - Cross-platform rendering and
       game engine.
     * [http://www.vassalengine.org/]Vassal - Vassal is a game engine for
       building and playing online adaptations of board games and card
       games. Play live on the Internet or by email. Vassal runs on all
       platforms, and is free, open-source software.
     * [http://waveengine.net/]Wave - Cross-platform engine written in C#
     * [https://github.com/WhitestormJS/whitestorm.js]WhiteStorm.js - 3d
       javacript framework for building apps and games
     * [http://mxa.codeplex.com/]XNA - Microsoft's game development
       framework.
     * [http://xenko.com/]Xenko - Open Source C# Game Engine.
     * [https://github.com/bkaradzic/bgfx]bgfx - Cross-platform, graphics
       API agnostic, "Bring Your Own Engine/Framework" style rendering
       library.
     * [http://gameplay3d.io/]gameplay - A free, open-source,
       cross-platform, 2D + 3D game framework written in C++. It is aimed
       towards indie game developers who are creating desktop and mobile
       games.
     * [http://ggez.rs/]ggez - A Rust library to create Good Games Easily.
     * [https://github.com/iioinc/iio.js]iio.js - A javascript library
       that speeds the creation and deployment of HTML5 Canvas
       applications
     * [http://jmonkeyengine.org/]jMonkeyEngine 3 - a 3D open-source game
       engine for adventurous Java developers.
     * [http://schteppe.github.io/p2.js/]p2.js - JavaScript 2D physics
       library
     * [http://voxeljs.com/]voxel.js - voxel.js is a collection of
       projects that make it easier than ever to create 3D voxel games
       like Minecraft all in the browser.

AI

     * [https://github.com/codecapers/Fluent-Behaviour-Tree]Fluent
       Behaviour Tree - C# behaviour tree library with a fluent API
       released under MIT.
     * [https://github.com/mgerhardy/simpleai/]SimpleAI - C++11 behaviour
       tree based library with a QT5 based remote debugger (and with
       optional LUA bindings) released under MIT.

Audio

   Audio editors, sounds collections and more.

Collections

     * [https://gamesounds.xyz/]Free Game Sounds - Archive of all kinds of
       royalty-free game sounds.
     * [http://www.freesound.org/]Freesound - collaborative database of
       Creative Commons Licensed sounds.
     * [https://musopen.org/]Musopen - Royalty free music.
     * [http://raisedbeaches.com/octave/index.html]Octave - free library
       of UI sounds.
     * [http://www.pacdv.com/sounds/index.html]PacDV - royalty free sounds
       collection.
     * [http://soundbible.com/]SoundBible.com - Royalty-free, searchable
       archive of sound effects under various licenses.

Music and Audio Editors

     * [http://sourceforge.net/projects/audacity/]Audacity - open source,
       cross-platform software for recording and editing sounds.
     * [http://www.audiosauna.com/]Audiosauna - transforms your web
       browser into a fast and flexible music production studio with built
       in synthesizers and live effects.
     * [http://www.audiotool.com/app]Audiotool - Online music producer.
     * [http://www.bfxr.net/]Bfxr - A tool to make sound effects for
       computer games.
     * [http://boscaceoil.net/]Bosca Ceoil - Online (and also desktop)
       music producer made by Terry Cavanagh. Simple, intuitive, has a
       distinctive retro-ish sound.
     * [http://sfbgames.com/chiptone/]ChipTone - Online sound effect
       generator
     * [http://famitracker.com/]FamiTracker - free windows tracker for
       producing music for the NES/Famicom-systems.
     * [http://tonematrix.audiotool.com/]iNudge - Create sound patterns
       online.
     * [http://jfxr.frozenfractal.com/]jfxr - A JavaScript port of the
       Bfxr sound effect generator.
     * [http://www.madtracker.org/main.php]MadTracker - a powerful and
       efficient approach to making music. Versatility and compatibility
       are guaranteed due to full VST(TM), ASIO(TM) and ReWire(TM)
       support.
     * [https://github.com/milkytracker/MilkyTracker]MilkyTracker - open
       source tracker for Mac/Linux/Windows platforms.
     * [http://www.drpetter.se/project_musagi.html]musagi - open source,
       fairly large and sophisticated music editor and synthesizer
     * [http://openmidiproject.osdn.jp/Sekaiju_en.html]Sekaiju - Open
       Source MIDI sequencer.
     * [https://soundation.com/]Soundation - Online Professional music
       studio.
     * [http://www.warmplace.ru/soft/sunvox/]SunVox - a small, fast and
       powerful modular synthesizer with pattern-based sequencer
       (tracker).

